    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carbon printing process that creates prints by superimposition of three monochromatic carbon plates in register. Each of these register plates is in a subtractive primary color, exposed from color separations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
